{
  "id": 5146265241387008,
  "name": "Clip Text overflow on user interaction",
  "summary": "When a user interacts (editing or caret navigation) with text which has ‘text-overflow: ellipsis’ set, the text switches temporarily from ellipsis to clip allowing the user to see and interact with the hidden overflow content. This feature applies to all editable and non-editable elements. For form controls (textarea, input), the behavior is already supported.",
